			<div class="body">
						<div class='body'><p>Chris -<br />
Your sister Audrey sent me a link to your site. April and my daughter Christina are the best of friends. Thank you for sharing your story and your struggle with the proper diagnosis. I too, had a similar struggle with being properly diagnosed with pseudo tumor cerebri over 10 years ago. It&#8217;s frustrating and unfair, but never lose faith.<br />
Last year, I trained with the Leukemia &amp; Lymphoma Society and walked my first half marathon raising more than $3800 for research and a cure to blood cancers. It was a struggle and, at times painful, but nothing compared to those who fight cancer every day. If you have not already, I would suggest contacting the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society for more information and support for you and your family <a href="http://www.lls.org/hm_lls" rel="nofollow">http://www.lls.org/hm_lls</a>. I walked to honor family and friends affected by cancer and next time I will walk for you.</p>
