			<div class="body">
						<div class='body'><p>Hi Christopher,<br />
We don&#8217;t know each other. I was referred to your website by (Col.) Jim Williams. Jim and I have served together on the board of the Intercultural Cancer Council for more than 10 years. I just wanted you to know that I&#8217;m a survivor of three different primary cancers. I was given five years to live and on May 22, 2009, I&#8217;ll celebrate my 23rd year of survival. God is good and prayers are powerful. I will be praying daily for you and your family. I, too, was misdiagnosed with my second cancer, allowing it to metastasize to many places. It&#8217;s been almost nine years since that time and I&#8217;m cancer free. Hang tough and never give up. I&#8217;m in Jacksonville, Florida and will be here cheering you on.</p>
<p>Keep the faith.</p>
<p>Bobbi de Córdova-Hanks</p>
